It's been years since I updated my review. After playing tons of tower defense games, this is really, HANDS DOWN, THE BEST! Even without cloud saving, this game is extremely fun & rewarding! Easily my favorite tower defense on the mobile platform, due to the level of polish.  However, this tower defense has a steep difficulty. Right off the bat, don't expect to play the first map on the hardest difficulty, as you'll have to slowly progress & start at the easiest difficulty, grinding in order to build up your available tower arsenal.  It's been a couple years now since the announcement, I CAN'T WAIT FOR THE SEQUEL! I just hope, they DON'T go the route, the rest of the mobile game market...the reason I love this game so much, is because it ISN'T a daily, online AD p2p. I just want a stand alone game that isn't online all the F'n time. Please keep gaming simple.

content: Better than the first by a long shot

This is a lot of fun, and quite addictive, for as long as the game lasts. The one real gripe is that hard mode isn't really hard enough; all but one of the time-trial maps are fairly easy to beat even without items after a few attempts. I've got thousands of coins/whatever that I have no actual use for. Bumping up the difficulty just a bit would really extend the longevity of the game.  I also find, so far, that the original Fieldrunners actually has more replay value. With just four maps it's easy to get into trying to improve your score or try different approaches; with so many maps here, there's really no incentive to revisit any one of them once you've beaten them.
A little grinding though.

Fieldrunners 2 is probably the best handheld tower defense on the market. After playing this one, most every android tower D pales in comparison.                                                               PROS: - Mixes "build your own mazes" with pre-built mazes - 3 bucks for a serious ammount of maps - A large variety of different weapons - The game is easy on easy, challenging on medium, and brutal on hard. ReplayValue++! - Perfect game for the train (or toilet) (pick up and play)                                                               CONS: - Long load times (probably for these graphics) - Bit of a memory hog - It's a big game (file size)                                                               The game does have inapp purchases, but as far as I can tell, they don't interfere with the game whatsoever. In the end, i'm very happy with my purchase, keep it up subatomic.  Quick tip: Use the spark tower!
